                  boolean useNoConflictCertificateData)
        Constructor that should be used when creating CA and retrieving CA info. Please use the shorter form if you do not need to set all of the values.
        Parameters:
        caid - ID of the CA
        defaultCertprofileId - the id of default cetificate profile for certificates this CA issues
        useNoConflictCertificateData - should use NoConflictCertificate data table to write to
        encodedValidity - the validity of this CA as a human-readable string, e.g. 25y
        catoken - the CA token for this CA, containing e.g. a reference to the crypto token
        description - a text describing this CA
        caSerialNumberOctetSize - serial number octet size for this CA
        crlperiod - the CRL validity period in ms
        crlIssueInterval - how often in ms the CRLs should be distributed, e.g. 3600000 will generate a new CRL every hour
        crlOverlapTime - the validity overlap in ms for a subsequent CRL, e.g. 5000 will generate a CRL 5m before the previous CRL expires
        deltacrlperiod - how often Delta CRLs should be distributed
        crlpublishers - a collection of publisher IDs for this CA
        keyValidators - a collection of key validator IDs for this CA
        useauthoritykeyidentifier - bool
        authoritykeyidentifiercritical - bool
        usecrlnumber - bool
        crlnumbercritical - bool
        defaultcrldistpoint - the URI of the default CRL distribution point
        defaultcrlissuer - Issuer
        defaultocspservicelocator - Locator
        crlAuthorityInformationAccess - Access info to CRLs
        certificateAiaDefaultCaIssuerUri - Issuer URI
        nameConstraintsPermitted - a list of name constraints which should be permitted
        nameConstraintsExcluded - a list of name constraints which should be excluded
        cadefinedfreshestcrl - CRL
        finishuser - bool
        extendedcaserviceinfos - bool
        useUTF8PolicyText - bool
        approvals - a map of approval profiles which should be used for different operations
        usePrintableStringSubjectDN - bool
        useLdapDnOrder - biik
        useCrlDistributionPointOnCrl - bool
        crlDistributionPointOnCrlCritical - bool
        includeInHealthCheck - enable healthcheck for this CA
        _doEnforceUniquePublicKeys - bool
        _doEnforceUniqueDistinguishedName - bool
        _doEnforceUniqueSubjectDNSerialnumber - bool
        _useCertReqHistory - bool
        _useUserStorage - bool
        _useCertificateStorage - bool
        _acceptRevocationNonExistingEntry - bool
        _cmpRaAuthSecret - bool
        keepExpiredCertsOnCRL - bool
